ompilable.\n- The `skeleton_code` must include import statements, global variables and constants, classes, and function signatures (with bodies replaced with `pass`).\n- For function signatures, follow the parameters listed in the SSAT.\n  - If a parameter has `\"default\": \"None\"`, write it as `=None` in the function signature.\n  - If a parameter has another default value, use that exact default.\n  - If `\"default\"` is missing, leave the parameter without a default.\n- Add the function description as a comment immediately under each function signature.\n- The imports and definitions should remain consistent with the provided previously generated skeletons.\n\n## Inputs:\n\n<Previously_Generated_Skeletons>\n```json\n[]\n```\n</Previously_Generated_Skeletons>\n\n<Target_File_SSAT>\n```json\n{'name': 'bplustree.h', 'path': 'lib/bplustree.h', 'description': 'Header file defining the core data structures and public API functions for the B+ tree implementation.', 'global_code': {'globalVariables': [{'name': 'MIN_CACHE_NUM', 'type': 'int', 'description': 'Minimum number of cache slots, set to 5.'}], 'globalBlocks': []}, 'classes': [{'name': 'bplus_tree', 'description': 'Main B+ tree structure holding cache, file descriptor, root offset, and free blocks list.', 'attributes': [], 'methods': [{'name': 'bplus_tree_init', 'description': 'Initialize a B+ tree from a file or create a new one.', 'return_type': 'struct bplus_tree*', 'parameters': [{'name': 'filename', 'type': 'const char*', 'description': 'The name of the file to store the B+ tree.'}, {'name': 'block_size', 'type': 'int', 'description': 'Configurable block size, must be a power of 2.'}]}, {'name': 'bplus_tree_deinit', 'description': 'Clean up tree resources and save metadata to boot file.', 'return_type': 'void', 'parameters': [{'name': 'tree', 'type': 'struct bplus_tree*', 'description': 'Pointer to the B+ tree to be deinitialized.'}]}, {'name': 'bplus_tree_get', 'description': 'Retrieve value associated with a given key.', 'return_type': 'long', 'parameters': [{'name': 'tree', 'type': 'struct bplus_tree*', 'description': 'Pointer to the B+ tree to be queried.'}, {'name': 'key', 'type': 'long', 'description': 'The key whose value is to be retrieved.'}]}, {'name': 'bplus_tree_put', 'description': 'Insert a key-value pair or delete a key-value pair if data is zero.', 'return_type': 'void', 'parameters': [{'name': 'tree', 'type': 'struct bplus_tree*', 'description': 'Pointer to the B+ tree where key-value pair is to be inserted or deleted.'}, {'name': 'key', 'type': 'long', 'description': 'The key to be inserted or deleted.'}, {'name': 'data', 'type': 'long', 'description': 'The value to be associated with the key; 0 indicates deletion.'}]}, {'name': 'bplus_tree_get_range', 'description': 'Retrieve sequences of values within a specified key range.', 'return_type': 'void', 'parameters': [{'name': 'tree', 'type': 'struct bplus_tree*', 'description': 'Pointer to the B+ tree to perform the range query on.'}, {'name': 'key1', 'type': 'long', 'description': 'The beginning of the key range.'}, {'name': 'key2', 'type': 'long', 'description': 'The end of the key range.'}]}]}, {'name': 'bplus_node', 'description': 'Node structure for B+ tree nodes, indicating self/parent/prev/next offsets, type, and children count.', 'attributes': [], 'methods': []}, {'name': 'free_block', 'description': 'Structure for tracking deleted blocks available for reuse in B+ tree management.', 'attributes': [], 'methods': []}, {'name': 'list_head', 'description': 'Doubly-linked list structure for managing free blocks in B+ tree.', 'attributes': [], 'methods': []}], 'functions': []}\n```\n</Target_File_SSAT>\n", "output_text": "{\"path\":\"lib/bplustree.h\",\"skeleton_code\":\"# Header file defining the core data structures and public API functions for the B+ tree implementation.\\n\\nMIN_CACHE_NUM = 5  # Minimum number of cache slots, set to 5.\\n\\nclass bplus_tree:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Main B+ tree structure holding cache, file descriptor, root offset, and free blocks list.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def bplus_tree_init(self, filename: 'const char*', block_size: int) -> 'struct bplus_tree*':\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Initialize a B+ tree from a file or create a new one.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        pass\\n\\n    def bplus_tree_deinit(self, tree: 'struct bplus_tree*') -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Clean up tree resources and save metadata to boot file.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        pass\\n\\n    def bplus_tree_get(self, tree: 'struct bplus_tree*', key: int) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Retrieve value associated with a given key.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        pass\\n\\n    def bplus_tree_put(self, tree: 'struct bplus_tree*', key: int, data: int) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Insert a key-value pair or delete a key-value pair if data is zero.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        pass\\n\\n    def bplus_tree_get_range(self, tree: 'struct bplus_tree*', key1: int, key2: int) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Retrieve sequences of values within a specified key range.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        pass\\n\\nclass bplus_node:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Node structure for B+ tree nodes, indicating self/parent/prev/next offsets, type, and children count.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    pass\\n\\nclass free_block:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Structure for tracking deleted blocks available for reuse in B+ tree management.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    pass\\n\\nclass list_head:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Doubly-linked list structure for managing free blocks in B+ tree.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    pass\\n\"}"}
